'''開普敦人種'''，是一位人类学家Carleton S. Coon 在1962年提出，用于形容[[开普敦|开普敦]]与[[卡拉哈里沙漠|卡拉哈里沙漠]]的原住民，他们是[[黑色人种|黑色人种]]中的特殊分类。<ref name="ReferenceA">''[[The_Origin_of_Races|The Origin of Races]]'' (1962) </ref><ref> Moore, Ruth ''Evolution'' (Life Nature Library) New York:1962 Time, Inc. Chapter 8: "The Emergence of Modern Homo Sapiens" Page 173--First page of picture section "Man and His Genes": The ''Capoid'' race is identified as one of the five major races of mankind, along with the ''[[Mongoloid_race|Mongoloid]]'', ''[[Negroid|Negroid]]'', ''[[Caucasoid_race|Caucasoid]]'', and ''[[Australoid|Australoid]]'' races (pictures of a person typical of each race are shown) </ref>

这是因为他们膚色偏黄，有[[蒙古褶|蒙古褶]]，与[[班图人|班图人]]很不同，所以有人提议用開普敦人種称呼他们。<ref name="ReferenceA"/>最近基因研究撒哈拉以南民族也与他们有关。最近有人认为他们与第一批走出非洲的[[智人|智人]]有关。

